NAME: blood aspartate aminotransferase activity level
DESCRIPTION: The amount of enzymatic activity of glutamic-oxaloacetic transaminase enzyme, commonly known as aspartate transaminase or aspartate aminotransferase (AST), in a specified sample of blood. AST catalyzes the reversible transfer of an amine group from l-glutamic acid to oxaloacetic acid, forming alpha-ketoglutaric acid and l-aspartic acid. Blood AST level is used as an enzymatic marker for liver disease or damage.

NAME: blood lactate dehydrogenase activity level
DESCRIPTION: The amount of ezymatic activity of lactate dehydrogenase (LDH) in a specified volume of blood. LDH is the enzyme which catalyses the reaction S)-lactate + NAD(+) <=> pyruvate + NADH. Blood LDH level can be used as a marker for tissue damage.

NAME: blood creatinine measurement
DESCRIPTION: blood creatinine measurement

NAME: blood carbon dioxide level
DESCRIPTION: The concentration of carbon dioxide (the product of the combustion of carbon with an excess of oxygen) in the blood.

NAME: blood creatine kinase activity level
DESCRIPTION: The amount of enzymatic activity of creatine kinase (CK) enzyme in a specified sample of blood. CK catalyses the reversible transfer of phosphate between ATP and various phosphogens such as creatine phosphate. Blood CK level is used as an enzymatic marker for myocardial infarction, rhabdomyolysis and acute renal failure.

NAME: Activated Partial Thromboplastin Time

NAME: Leukemic Blasts/Lymphocytes
DESCRIPTION: A relative measurement (ratio or percentage)  of the leukemic blasts (immature lymphoblasts) to mature lymphocytes in a biological specimen.

NAME: Leukocyte esterase
DESCRIPTION: A quantitative measurement of the amount of leukocyte esterase present in a sample.

NAME: Leukocytes
DESCRIPTION: A measurement of the leukocytes per unit of a biological specimen.

NAME: Lymphocytes Atypical
DESCRIPTION: A measurement of the atypical lymphocytes per unit of a biological specimen.

NAME: Lymphocytes Atypical/Leukocytes
DESCRIPTION: A relative measurement (ratio or percentage) of the atypical lymphocytes to leukocytes in a biological specimen.

NAME: Lymphocytes/Leukocytes
DESCRIPTION: A relative measurement (ratio or percentage) of the lymphocytes to leukocytes in a biological specimen.

NAME: Lymphoma Cells
DESCRIPTION: A measurement of the malignant lymphocytes in a biological specimen.

NAME: Lymphoma Cells/Lymphocytes
DESCRIPTION: A relative measurement (ratio or percentage) of the malignant lymphocytes to all lymphocytes in a biological specimen.

NAME: Macrocytes
DESCRIPTION: A measurement of the macrocytes per unit of a biological specimen.

NAME: Magnesium
DESCRIPTION: A quantitative measurement of the amount of magnesium present in a sample.

NAME: Malignant Cells, NOS
DESCRIPTION: A measurement of the malignant cells of all types in a biological specimen.

NAME: Malignant Cells, NOS/Blood Cells
DESCRIPTION: A relative measurement (ratio or percentage) of the malignant cells of all types to all blood cells in a biological specimen.

NAME: blood urea nitrogen level
DESCRIPTION: The level of urea in the blood in terms of nitrogen content; converted to urea concentration by multiplying by 60/28 or 2.14. Urea is the chief nitrogenous end product of protein metabolism in whole blood. Urea is formed in the liver from amino acids and from ammonia compounds and can be found in urine, blood, and lymph.

NAME: blood high density lipoprotein cholesterol level
DESCRIPTION: Measurement of the amount of cholesterol, a eukaryotic sterol that in higher animals is the precursor of bile acids and steroid hormones and a key constituent of cell membranes, carried in high-density lipoprotein (HDL) molecules in a specified volume of blood, the fluid that circulates through the heart, arteries, capillaries and veins carrying nutrients and oxygen to the body tissues and metabolites away from them. HDL is the smallest of the major lipoprotein particles, complex molecules that consist of a protein membrane surrounding a core of lipids. The HDL class of lipoproteins, specifically the subtypes of HDL2 and HDL3, have densities between 1.063 and 1.210 g/ml.

NAME: Mature Plasma Cells
DESCRIPTION: A measurement of the mature plasma cells (plasmacytes) in a biological specimen.

NAME: Mature Plasma Cells/Lymphocytes
DESCRIPTION: A relative measurement (ratio or percentage) of the mature plasma cells (plasmacytes) to all lymphocytes in a biological specimen.

NAME: May-Hegglin Anomaly
DESCRIPTION: A measurement of the May-Hegglin Anomaly (which is characterized by large, misshapen platelets and the presence of Dohle bodies in the leukocytes) in a blood specimen.

NAME: Mean Platelet Volume
DESCRIPTION: A measurement of the average size of the platelets found in a blood specimen.

NAME: Metamyelocytes
DESCRIPTION: A measurement of the metamyelocytes (small, myelocytic neutrophils with an indented nucleus) in a biological specimen.

NAME: Metamyelocytes/Leukocytes
DESCRIPTION: A relative measurement (ratio or percentage )of the metamyelocytes (small, myelocytic neutrophils with an indented nucleus) to all leukocytes  in a biological specimen.

NAME: Microcytes
DESCRIPTION: A measurement of the microcytes per unit of a biological specimen.

NAME: Monoblasts
DESCRIPTION: A measurement of the monoblast cells per unit of a biological specimen.

NAME: Monoblasts/Leukocytes
DESCRIPTION: A relative measurement (ratio or percentage) of monoblast cells to all leukocytes in a biological specimen.

NAME: Monocytes
DESCRIPTION: A measurement of the monocytes per unit of a biological specimen.

NAME: Monocytes/Leukocytes
DESCRIPTION: A relative measure (ratio or percentage) of the monocytes to leukocytes in a biological specimen.

NAME: Myeloblasts
DESCRIPTION: A measurement of the myeloblast cells per unit of a biological specimen.

NAME: Myeloblasts/Leukocytes
DESCRIPTION: A relative measurement (ratio or percentage) of the myeloblasts to leukocytes in a biological specimen.

NAME: Myelocytes
DESCRIPTION: A measurement of the myelocytes per unit of a biological specimen.

NAME: Myelocytes/Leukocytes
DESCRIPTION: A relative measurement (ratio or percentage) of the myelocytes to leukocytes in a biological specimen.

NAME: Myoglobin
DESCRIPTION: A measurement of myoglobin in a biological specimen.

NAME: Neutrophilic Metamyelocytes
DESCRIPTION: A measurement of the neutrophilic metamyelocytes in a biological specimen.

NAME: Neutrophilic Myelocytes
DESCRIPTION: A measurement of the neutrophilic myelocytes in a biological specimen.

NAME: Neutrophils Band Form
DESCRIPTION: A measurement of the banded neutrophils per unit of a biological specimen.

NAME: Neutrophils Band Form/Leukocytes
DESCRIPTION: A relative measurement (ratio or percentage) of the banded neutrophils to leukocytes in a biological specimen.

NAME: Neutrophils, Segmented
DESCRIPTION: A measurement of the segmented neutrophils in a biological specimen.

NAME: Neutrophils, Segmented/Leukocytes
DESCRIPTION: A relative measurement (ratio or percentage) of segmented neutrophils to leukocytes in a biological specimen.

NAME: blood low density lipoprotein cholesterol level
DESCRIPTION: Measurement of the amount of cholesterol, a eukaryotic sterol that in higher animals is the precursor of bile acids and steroid hormones and a key constituent of cell membranes, carried in low-density lipoprotein (LDL) molecules in a specified volume of blood, the fluid that circulates through the heart, arteries, capillaries and veins carrying nutrients and oxygen to the body tissues and metabolites away from them. LDL constitute a class of relatively large, heterogeneous lipoprotein particles, complex molecules that consist of a protein membrane surrounding a core of lipids. The LDL class of lipoproteins has a density between 1.019 and 1.063 g/ml. In some animal species, such as canine and rodents, this may overlap with the HDL1 class and be designated LDL/HDL1.

NAME: blood triglyceride level
DESCRIPTION: The amount of triglycerides in a specific volume of blood, the fluid that circulates through the heart, arteries, capillaries and veins carrying nutrients and oxygen to the body tissues and metabolites away from them. Triglycerides are any of a group of lipids that are esters formed from one molecule of glycerol and three molecules of one or more fatty acids, are widespread in adipose tissue, and commonly circulate in the blood in the form of lipoproteins.

NAME: blood fibrinogen level
DESCRIPTION: Measurement of the amount of fibrinogen in blood, the fluid that circulates through the heart, arteries, capillaries and veins carrying nutrients and oxygen to the body tissues and metabolites away from them. Fibrinogen is a glycoprotein comprised of three pairs of nonidentical polypeptide chains; cleavage products of fibrinogen have a major role in blood clotting as well as roles in cell adhesion and spreading, display vasoconstrictor activity, and can function as chemotactic and mitogenic agents for several cell types.

NAME: blood potassium level
DESCRIPTION: The amount of potassium ions in a specified volume of blood.

NAME: Neutrophils/Leukocytes
DESCRIPTION: A relative measurement (ratio or percentage) of the neutrophils to leukocytes in a biological specimen.

NAME: Nitrite
DESCRIPTION: A quantitative measurement of the amount of nitrite present in a sample.

NAME: Nucleated Erythrocytes
DESCRIPTION: A measurement of the nucleated red blood cells (large, immature nucleated erythrocytes) in a biological specimen.

NAME: Nucleated Erythrocytes/Erythrocytes
DESCRIPTION: A relative measurement (ratio or percentage) of the nucleated red blood cells (large, immature nucleated erythrocytes) to all erythrocytes in a biological specimen.

NAME: Nucleated Erythrocytes/Leukocytes
DESCRIPTION: A relative measurement (ratio or percentage) of nucleated erythrocytes to leukocytes in a biological specimen.

NAME: Panel Reactive Antibody
DESCRIPTION: An assessment of the reactivity between host immune cells and donor human leukocyte antigen. This test is most commonly carried out in subjects awaiting transplant. The recipient's blood or serum is mixed with either a panel of lymphocytes from random blood donations or a potential donor's purified human leukocyte antigens (HLA). Host reactivity is scored as a percent.

NAME: Pappenheimer Bodies
DESCRIPTION: A measurement of the Pappenheimer Bodies (violet or blue staining, ferritin granules usually found along the periphery of the red blood cells) in a biological specimen.

NAME: Parathyroid Hormone, Intact
DESCRIPTION: A measurement of the intact parathyroid hormone (consisting of amino acids 1-84 or 7-84) in a biological specimen.

NAME: Partial thromboplastin time
DESCRIPTION: A measurement of the length of time that it takes for clotting to occur when reagents are added to a plasma specimen. The test is partial due to the absence of tissue factor (Factor III) from the reaction mixture.

NAME: Pelger Huet Anomaly
DESCRIPTION: A measurement of the Pelger Huet Anomaly (neutrophils and eosinophils nuclei appear rodlike, spherical or dumbbell shapped) in a biological specimen.

NAME: Pemphigoid Antibodies
DESCRIPTION: A measurement of the pemphigoid antibodies in a biological specimen.

NAME: Phosphate
DESCRIPTION: A measurement of the phosphate in a biological specimen.

NAME: Plasmacytoid Lymphocytes
DESCRIPTION: A measurement of the plasmacytoid lymphocytes (lymphocytes with peripherally clumped chromatin and often deep blue cytoplasm, and that appear similar to plasma cells) in a biological specimen.

NAME: Plasmacytoid Lymphocytes/Lymphocytes
DESCRIPTION: A relative measurement (ratio or percentage) of the plasmacytoid lymphocytes (lymphocytes with peripherally clumped chromatin and often deep blue cytoplasm, and that appear similar to plasma cells) to all lymphocytes in a biological specimen.

NAME: Plasminogen Activator Inhibitor-1 Antigen
DESCRIPTION: A measurement of the plasminogen activator inhibitor-1 antigen in a biological specimen.

NAME: Platelet Distribution Width
DESCRIPTION: A mesurement of the range of platelet sizes in a blood specimen.

NAME: Poikilocytes
DESCRIPTION: A measurement of the odd-shaped erythrocytes in a whole blood specimen.

NAME: Poikilocytes/Erythrocytes
DESCRIPTION: A relative measurement (ratio or percentage) of the poikilocytes irregularly shaped erythrocytes to all erythrocytes in a biological specimen.

NAME: Polychromasia
DESCRIPTION: A measurement of the blue-staining characteristic of newly generated erythrocytes.

NAME: Polymorphonuclear leukocyte count
DESCRIPTION: Polymorphonuclear leukocyte count

NAME: Potassium
DESCRIPTION: A measurement of the potassium in a biological specimen.

NAME: blood chloride level
DESCRIPTION: The amount of chloride ions in a specified volume of blood.

NAME: blood sodium level
DESCRIPTION: The amount of sodium ions in a specified volume of blood.

NAME: blood calcium level
DESCRIPTION: The amount of calcium ions in a specified volume of blood.

NAME: blood phosphate level
DESCRIPTION: The amount of phosphorus, measured as inorganic phosphate, in a specified sample of blood.

NAME: blood magnesium level
DESCRIPTION: blood magnesium level

NAME: blood alanine aminotransferase activity level
DESCRIPTION: The amount of enzymatic activity of glutamic-pyruvate transaminase enzyme, commonly known as alanine transaminase or alanine aminotransferase (ALT), enzyme in a specified sample of blood. ALT catalyzes the reversible transamination between alanine and 2-oxoglutarate to generate pyruvate and glutamate. Blood ALT level is used as an enzymatic marker for  liver disease or damage.

NAME: blood alkaline phosphatase activity level
DESCRIPTION: Quantitation of the catalytic effect exerted by alkaline phosphatase (AP) in a specified sample of blood. AP is an enzyme that catalyzes the cleavage of orthophosphate from orthophosphoric monoesters under alkaline conditions.
